Class StdCSV

  • java.lang.Object
    • StdCSV
  • public class StdCSV
extends java.lang.Object
    This java file takes a CSV file as an input with a flag to say whether the data is in columns, and whether the UTF (random characters) signature is in the data. After which, it will store the data with the headers as a "key" in a Symbol Table, and the values of each header in a double array as the data type.
